THE highly-anticipated Young, Famous & African reality TV show has released a trailer. The show, starring Khanyi Mbau, Diamond Platnumz, Annie Macaulay-Idibia, Innocent “2baba” Idibia, Nadia Nakai, Swanky Jerry, Zari The Boss Lady, Naked DJ, Kayleigh Schwark and Andile Ncube, will hit the screens on Friday, 18 February. Announcing the show, Netflix said it would show A-listers from around the African continent. “Unscripted and unapologetically African, the series promises to bring viewers top-tier, variety entertainment through the lens of some of their favourite personalities from all over the continent,” read the statement. “From rivalries, new friendships and romantic connections to stories that made the headlines and delicious tea being spilled, stars will give you an intimate insider look into their glamorous lives as they navigate Joburg.” ALSO READ : KHANYI SPEAKS ABOUT THE WIFE 'CHALLENGES'! The seven-episode show was produced by Urban Brew Studios, with co-creators and executive producers Martin Asare Amankwa and Peace Hyde. Martin said: “It’s really exciting to be able to show the world an exclusive look into the lives of Africa’s top celebrities and socialites. Young, Famous & African is a depiction of a world that has never been seen before, highlighting authentic stories and unrivalled access to some of the most celebrated celebrities.” Cast member Ugandan media personality Zari said she couldn’t wait for people to see the show. “I’m excited for people to see how much of ourselves we poured into this show, showcasing our true, authentic trials and tribulations. Young, Famous & African will give our fans an inside look into our entertaining and busy lives.” Watch the trailer below: "It's glitz. It's glamour and just a touch of ??". You can't miss this. Young, Famous and African arrives March 18. Only on Netflix. pic.twitter.com/zPU1jeTMuB 